This is a modal window. Beginning of dialog window. Escape will cancel and close the window. End of dialog window. The Seme- Krake border is one of the major opened crossing points established between Benin Republic and Nigeria. It is one of the economical ‘lungs’ of Benin Customs system. The ECOWAS vehicle insurance and the laissez-passer are a must important documents. The border (Juxtaposed Zone) is secured by all units of both national Custom and Police authorities (Benin and Nigeria). Passing goods and trucks must be inspected by the National Police and custom agents. (NAN)